Nepali Chief of Army Staff Resigns 
Nepali Chief of the Army Staff General Gadul Sumsher J.B. Rana extended
his resignation to King Birendra who has accepted it, the official
daily "The Rising Nepal" reported today.
The paper said that General Rana submitted his resignation Thursday on
moral ground to maintain the image of the Royal Nepalese Army as well
as the prestige and dignity of the office of chief of the army staff in
the context of the case of corruption and financial irregularities.
